Is that even possible. Sam?

756
00:52:52.050 --> 00:52:53.969
Yes. but at what cost?

757
00:52:55.762 --> 00:52:57.389
I'll have to pay.

758
00:52:59.141 --> 00:53:00.600
Really?

759
00:53:00.642 --> 00:53:02.060
I think so.

760
00:53:03.270 --> 00:53:05.605
Where is this going to come back to us?

761
00:53:06.398 --> 00:53:07.482
Everywhere.

762
00:53:08.316 --> 00:53:12.904
Sam. I don't think you seem to understand
what your boy here has just said.

763
00:53:16.658 --> 00:53:18.326
If I made you.

764
00:53:19.119 --> 00:53:20.829
how would you do this?

765
00:53:26.710 --> 00:53:29.950
You call the traders in for their normal
6:30 meeting and you be honest with them.

766
00:53:30.005 --> 00:53:32.507
Because they're going to know
it's the end either way.

767
00:53:32.716 --> 00:53:35.719
You're going to have to throw them a bone.
and a pretty big one.

768
00:53:35.802 --> 00:53:38.221
And then you've got to
come out of the gates storming.

769
00:53:38.305 --> 00:53:40.557
No swaps. No nothing.

770
00:53:40.640 --> 00:53:42.934
40% done by 10:15. By 11:00.

771
00:53:43.018 --> 00:53:44.478
all your trades have to be gone

772
00:53:44.519 --> 00:53:46.938
because by lunchtime.
word's going to be out.

773
00:53:47.939 --> 00:53:52.027
And by 2:00 you're going to be selling
at 65 cents on the dollar. if you're lucky.

774
00:53:52.068 --> 00:53:55.131
And then the feds are going to be in here.
up your ass. trying to slow you down.

775
00:53:55.155 --> 00:53:56.364
Ramesh?

776
00:53:56.448 --> 00:53:59.034
They can slow you down.
They can't stop you.

777
00:53:59.075 --> 00:54:00.368
It's yours to sell.

778
00:54:00.410 --> 00:54:02.579
But. John. even if

779
00:54:03.538 --> 00:54:06.792
we manage to pull that off.
and that's saying something.

780
00:54:08.376 --> 00:54:11.379
the real question is.
who are we selling this to?

781
00:54:11.880 --> 00:54:14.466
Same people we've been selling it to
the last two years.

782
00:54:14.549 --> 00:54:16.176
and whoever else will buy it.

783
00:54:16.218 --> 00:54:18.553
But. John. if you do this.

784
00:54:19.971 --> 00:54:22.933
you will kill the market for years. It's over.

785
00:54:25.185 --> 00:54:28.104
And you're selling something
that you know has no value.

786
00:54:28.563 --> 00:54:33.026
We are selling to willing buyers
of the current fair market price.

787
00:54:33.735 --> 00:54:37.197
So that we may survive.

788
00:54:37.239 --> 00:54:41.076
You will never sell anything
to any of those people ever again.

789
00:54:41.159 --> 00:54:42.452
I understand.

790
00:54:42.577 --> 00:54:44.371
- Do you?
- Do you?

791
00:54:45.622 --> 00:54:47.207
This is it!

792
00:54:47.249 --> 00:54:49.543
I'm telling you. This is it.

793
00:55:00.929 --> 00:55:02.305
Now. it's 4:00.

794
00:55:02.931 --> 00:55:06.059
Jared. you've got till 5:00 to
break this down and draw me up a plan.

795
00:55:06.101 --> 00:55:10.397
Is there anybody else who knows what's
in here at the moment. block by block?

796
00:55:11.106 --> 00:55:12.440
SARAH: Eric Dale.

797
00:55:13.024 --> 00:55:14.192
TULD: And where is he?

798
00:55:14.609 --> 00:55:17.362
As of today. he's no longer with the firm.

799
00:55:17.696 --> 00:55:20.156
We have been trying to locate him.

800
00:55:24.077 --> 00:55:25.120
- Carmelo.
- Yes.

801
00:55:25.203 --> 00:55:27.289
Get me Eric Dale here by 6:30.

802
00:55:27.789 --> 00:55:29.040
It's done.

803
00:55:29.332 --> 00:55:31.334
We meet back here in an hour.

804
00:55:33.795 --> 00:55:35.547
Sam. let's talk.

805
00:55:48.810 --> 00:55:50.854
TULD: This is a hell of a town.

806
00:55:52.689 --> 00:55:55.692
I've always loved this place.
since the day I arrived.

807
00:55:55.775 --> 00:55:57.152
Everything about it.

808
00:56:06.036 --> 00:56:08.830
Sam. are you going to go with me on this?

809
00:56:10.707 --> 00:56:12.500
I don't know. John.

810
00:56:14.294 --> 00:56:16.171
This one is very ugly.

811
00:56:17.839 --> 00:56:19.883
You and I. we're salesmen.

812
00:56:20.675 --> 00:56:23.303
We sell. That's what we do.
It's not complicated.

813
00:56:23.345 --> 00:56:24.638
Exactly.

814
00:56:25.472 --> 00:56:28.058
And you know damn well
you don't sell anything to anybody

815
00:56:28.141 --> 00:56:30.101
unless you think they're gonna
come back for more.

816
00:56:30.143 --> 00:56:33.396
That's the lesson we learned.
And tomorrow. we're done.

817
00:56:33.939 --> 00:56:35.065
But this is it. Sam.

818
00:56:35.148 --> 00:56:37.359
You keep saying that.
What's that supposed to mean?

819
00:56:37.692 --> 00:56:39.444
This is the big one.

820
00:56:40.111 --> 00:56:42.906
Most of us aren't going to
make it out of this one.

821
00:56:42.989 --> 00:56:45.033
- Us?
- The Street.

822
00:56:46.034 --> 00:56:47.494
What are you talking about?

823
00:56:47.869 --> 00:56:50.549
This isn't the last situation
I'm gonna have to deal with this week.

824
00:56:50.622 --> 00:56:51.831
This is just the start.

825
00:56:52.374 --> 00:56:54.209
It's the start 'cause you're starting it.

826
00:56:54.542 --> 00:56:57.587
Maybe. But I don't believe that.
Not this time.

827
00:56:58.380 --> 00:57:00.590
The numbers.
they just don't add up anymore.

828
00:57:00.674 --> 00:57:04.219
I agree with you there.
I've been saying that for years.

829
00:57:04.260 --> 00:57:07.555
If this kid out there can
come up with this. then...

830
00:57:08.556 --> 00:57:11.309
Look. I just don't think I can walk in there
knowing what I know

831
00:57:11.393 --> 00:57:13.061
and put the hammer down on these guys.

832
00:57:14.062 --> 00:57:16.231
When did you start getting so soft. Sam?

833
00:57:16.773 --> 00:57:19.609
Fuck you. soft. You're panicking.

834
00:57:22.404 --> 00:57:26.825
If you're the first out of the door.
that's not called panicking.

835
00:57:32.747 --> 00:57:36.584
You're obviously operating
with more information than I have.

836
00:57:38.420 --> 00:57:41.131
But I think this will destroy this firm.

837
00:57:41.631 --> 00:57:43.216
No one will ever trust you again.

838
00:57:43.258 --> 00:57:46.094
You're knowingly putting people
out of business. full stop.

839
00:57:48.763 --> 00:57:51.057
You let me deal with that. Sam.

840
00:58:06.114 --> 00:58:07.198
How'd it go?

841
00:58:08.241 --> 00:58:10.368
This is a fucking shit show.

842
00:58:11.202 --> 00:58:13.747
- They're gonna go with it?
- Probably.

843
00:58:14.622 --> 00:58:15.790
Jesus.

844
00:58:17.542 --> 00:58:19.461
Remember this day. boys.

845
00:58:21.629 --> 00:58:23.298
Remember this day.

846
00:58:38.980 --> 00:58:41.149
So. what's the strategy here?

847
00:58:41.232 --> 00:58:42.543
That's where I'm headed right now.

848
00:58:42.567 --> 00:58:44.402
Downstairs to work on it with my guys.

849
00:58:44.486 --> 00:58:46.988
No. no. You and I with John.

850
00:58:52.744 --> 00:58:57.165
I'm not sure that we need one. Sarah.
That's not the way I do things.

851
00:58:57.207 --> 00:58:58.458
Please.

852
00:59:00.668 --> 00:59:03.546
Listen. he knows where we've stood on this

853
00:59:03.630 --> 00:59:05.006
all along.

854
00:59:05.673 --> 00:59:07.634
That's exactly my point.

855
00:59:08.176 --> 00:59:11.888
And knowing what was discussed
by both you and I.

856
00:59:12.388 --> 00:59:15.475
I don't see how this could
provide you with anything

857
00:59:15.517 --> 00:59:18.269
other than a false sense of comfort.

858
00:59:18.353 --> 00:59:21.606
I'm not looking for
a sense of comfort here. Sarah.

859
00:59:22.690 --> 00:59:25.360
I don't think there's one to be found.

860
00:59:35.870 --> 00:59:37.914
So. again. what's the strategy here?

861
00:59:40.416 --> 00:59:42.919
I'm just not sure
there's much more to do on this.

862
00:59:43.962 --> 00:59:45.630
It's very simple.

863
00:59:46.172 --> 00:59:49.050
Don't even think about fucking me on this.

864
00:59:50.093 --> 00:59:52.220
'Cause if we're going down.

865
00:59:53.346 --> 00:59:55.515
then you damn well know it'll be together.

866
00:59:57.142 --> 00:59:58.226
No.

867
00:59:59.060 --> 01:00:00.979
I'm not sure that I do know that.

868
01:00:01.855 --> 01:00:03.523
(ELEVATOR WARNING BEEP)

869
01:00:23.126 --> 01:00:24.252
Hey.

870
01:00:24.919 --> 01:00:26.421
Oh. I'm sorry.

871
01:00:40.059 --> 01:00:42.937
What do you guys think
Tuld made last year?

872
01:00:45.023 --> 01:00:46.691
Would you shut the fuck up?

873
01:00:46.774 --> 01:00:48.234
86 million.

874
01:00:49.485 --> 01:00:51.487
In bonuses and salary.

875
01:00:52.447 --> 01:00:54.324
- Really?
- Sure. it's public record.

876
01:00:54.407 --> 01:00:56.701
That is a lot of fucking money.

877
01:00:57.911 --> 01:00:59.621
He was worth a billion.

878
01:00:59.704 --> 01:01:00.705
Was?

879
01:01:01.956 --> 01:01:03.291
Till today.

880
01:01:04.125 --> 01:01:05.376
PETER: Really?

881
01:01:06.961 --> 01:01:08.338
You'll see.

882
01:01:11.299 --> 01:01:14.135
I'm going to get some coffee.
You guys want anything else?

883
01:01:14.219 --> 01:01:17.055
- I'm all right.
- I could use some real air.

884
01:01:17.138 --> 01:01:19.200
- SETH: Probably a good idea.
- Is it all right. Will?

885
01:01:19.224 --> 01:01:21.160
- Is what all right?
- If I get out of here for a minute?

886
01:01:21.184 --> 01:01:22.936
Of course. it's not a prison.

887
01:01:22.977 --> 01:01:25.230
You want me to hold your hand?

888
01:01:29.859 --> 01:01:32.528
Why did they put all this fruit on it?

889
01:01:34.656 --> 01:01:36.157
(PHONE RINGING)

890
01:01:41.913 --> 01:01:43.957
Hello. Will Emerson.

891
01:01:43.998 --> 01:01:45.166
Hello.

892
01:01:48.795 --> 01:01:50.046
Right.

893
01:01:51.381 --> 01:01:53.758
No. thank you. I understand.

894
01:01:56.344 --> 01:01:58.304
No. we'll be discreet.

895
01:01:59.847 --> 01:02:01.182
Thank you.

896
01:02:01.849 --> 01:02:03.559
- What?
- Eric's wife.

897
01:02:04.102 --> 01:02:06.205
He's alive. he's home.
he doesn't want to speak to us.

898
01:02:06.229 --> 01:02:07.709
and he doesn't know that she rang me.

899
01:02:07.772 --> 01:02:09.440
- Where's he live?
- Heights.

900
01:02:09.857 --> 01:02:11.526
- Shall I call Tuld's guy?
- No.

901
01:02:12.026 --> 01:02:14.421
It's Eric. The last thing we need
is those guys going over there.

902
01:02:14.445 --> 01:02:15.881
No. you two go get him
and try to bring him here.

903
01:02:15.905 --> 01:02:18.366
- But you got to be back by 6:00 am.
- All right.

904
01:02:21.661 --> 01:02:23.329
I hate Brooklyn.

905
01:02:27.333 --> 01:02:28.376
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

906
01:02:28.418 --> 01:02:29.460
TULD: May I come in?

907
01:02:29.544 --> 01:02:31.713
Of course. Please. sit down.

908
01:02:32.213 --> 01:02:33.756
(DOOR CLOSING)

909
01:02:37.593 --> 01:02:38.636
So...

910
01:02:38.886 --> 01:02:39.887
(CHUCKLES)

911
01:02:42.807 --> 01:02:45.018
We're going to do this thing.

912
01:02:48.146 --> 01:02:49.314
Okay.

913
01:02:50.606 --> 01:02:52.608
It's going to be tight.

914
01:02:54.402 --> 01:02:55.945
Is Sam on board?

915
01:02:56.321 --> 01:02:57.613
Not yet.

916
01:03:01.409 --> 01:03:02.744
Sarah.

917
01:03:03.369 --> 01:03:07.373
I need a head to feed to the traders
on the floor and the board.

918
01:03:12.086 --> 01:03:14.047
Is it me or Cohen?

919
01:03:14.088 --> 01:03:15.423
It's you.

920
01:03:25.099 --> 01:03:29.020
Of course. you're well aware
that I filtered several warnings

921
01:03:29.103 --> 01:03:31.773
to you and Cohen about this a year ago.

922
01:03:32.231 --> 01:03:36.652
I really don't think that's the best path
for you to take at this point.

923
01:03:40.698 --> 01:03:43.618
You're going to be well taken care of here.

924
01:03:46.329 --> 01:03:48.122
Obviously. it is

925
01:03:49.165 --> 01:03:50.166
quite complicated.

926
01:03:50.249 --> 01:03:52.377
John. I was told under no uncertain terms...

927
01:03:52.460 --> 01:03:54.629
It was always a very gray area.

928
01:03:54.670 --> 01:03:59.759
Actually. it was made very clear at the time
by you. me. and Cohen.

929
01:04:01.677 --> 01:04:05.264
I'd really appreciate it
if you didn't fight me on this.

930
01:04:17.443 --> 01:04:20.071
We all fucked this one up pretty good.

931
01:04:20.905 --> 01:04:22.073
Yes.

932
01:04:24.450 --> 01:04:26.494
We need you to stay here
until this is finished

933
01:04:26.536 --> 01:04:28.830
and the market's closed.

934
01:04:28.871 --> 01:04:30.331
I understand.

935
01:04:32.667 --> 01:04:36.212
They'll go over the numbers
with you downstairs.

936
01:04:36.295 --> 01:04:37.630
Good luck.

937
01:04:37.672 --> 01:04:39.841
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

938
01:04:55.314 --> 01:04:57.316
Oh. fuck. Jared's coming.

939
01:04:58.568 --> 01:05:00.695
What's the boy wonder want?

940
01:05:06.534 --> 01:05:08.953
- You got a minute?
- Just off to pick up Eric.

941
01:05:09.036 --> 01:05:10.788
Yeah. I know. It will only take a second.

942
01:05:10.872 --> 01:05:12.206
All right. what is it?

943
01:05:12.540 --> 01:05:14.917
Tuld and I have concerns that Sam

944
01:05:15.001 --> 01:05:17.962
may not be willing to step up
and do the right thing here.

945
01:05:18.379 --> 01:05:19.797
This has never been a problem.

946
01:05:19.881 --> 01:05:20.923
No. it hasn't.

947
01:05:21.132 --> 01:05:24.427
But sometimes.
in acute situations such as this.

948
01:05:24.510 --> 01:05:29.891
often what is right can take on
multiple interpretations.

949
01:05:33.895 --> 01:05:35.396
Sam will step up.

950
01:05:35.480 --> 01:05:38.232
Oh. I know he will. But if he doesn't...

951
01:05:39.775 --> 01:05:42.945
But if he doesn't.
we need to know that you will.

952
01:05:45.114 --> 01:05:46.115
Thank you.

953
01:05:46.199 --> 01:05:48.618
You need to know that I will what?

954
01:05:48.701 --> 01:05:50.453
That you'll step up.

955
01:05:52.121 --> 01:05:54.999
I have no doubt that
Sam will make the right decision.

956
01:05:55.082 --> 01:05:56.751
But just to make it clear.

957
01:05:56.792 --> 01:05:59.504
he and I have always had
the same interpretation of what's right.

958
01:06:01.589 --> 01:06:04.091
no matter how acute the situation.

959
01:06:16.938 --> 01:06:18.898
(PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

960
01:07:24.839 --> 01:07:26.299
(MUSIC STOPS)

961
01:08:50.257 --> 01:08:51.926
Jesus. that's a nice place.

962
01:08:51.967 --> 01:08:54.261
Yeah. it is. He just bought it.

963
01:08:55.888 --> 01:08:57.640
I hope it was with cash.

964
01:08:58.766 --> 01:09:01.435
Fuck me.
you're a heartless little shit sometimes.

965
01:09:03.270 --> 01:09:04.772
And it wasn't.

966
01:09:06.607 --> 01:09:08.943
Don't touch any of the buttons.

967
01:09:15.366 --> 01:09:17.618
- What are you doing here?
- Hey.

968
01:09:24.458 --> 01:09:27.628
So. Peter finished the model
you were working on.

969
01:09:28.295 --> 01:09:29.463
Really?

970
01:09:29.922 --> 01:09:31.424
It caused a shit storm.

971
01:09:31.924 --> 01:09:33.384
I bet it did.

972
01:09:34.468 --> 01:09:35.803
You think he's right?

973
01:09:36.595 --> 01:09:38.264
I know he's right.

974
01:09:40.516 --> 01:09:41.600
Fuck.

975
01:09:43.644 --> 01:09:44.979
All right.

976
01:09:50.151 --> 01:09:52.486
So Jared Cohen called
an emergency meeting

977
01:09:52.570 --> 01:09:54.196
with the senior partners last night.

978
01:09:54.488 --> 01:09:56.866
And based on your findings.

979
01:09:56.949 --> 01:10:00.161
they've decided to liquidate
our entire position.

980
01:10:00.745 --> 01:10:01.746
Today.

981
01:10:04.248 --> 01:10:06.292
I'm very sorry about that.

982
01:10:12.757 --> 01:10:15.926
They're worried about you being out here
and they want me to bring you back.

983
01:10:16.635 --> 01:10:17.845
Please.

984
01:10:18.429 --> 01:10:20.181
I'm just saying.

985
01:10:20.222 --> 01:10:21.807
- Fuck them. Fuck them.
- Eric...

986
01:10:21.849 --> 01:10:24.518
- Don't be rash.
- Forget it. I signed my paper. I'm out.

987
01:10:24.602 --> 01:10:27.104
- They'll pay you.
- They got nothing on me.

988
01:10:27.188 --> 01:10:28.272
They'll pay you.

989
01:10:29.148 --> 01:10:31.358
I've been paid enough already.

990
01:10:35.446 --> 01:10:36.572
Fuck.

991
01:10:39.867 --> 01:10:42.328
Do you know I built a bridge once?

992
01:10:43.120 --> 01:10:44.830
- Sorry?
- A bridge.

993
01:10:46.040 --> 01:10:47.792
No. I didn't know that.

994
01:10:47.875 --> 01:10:50.085
I was an engineer by trade.

995
01:10:52.338 --> 01:10:56.383
It went from Dilles Bottom. Ohio.
to Moundsville. West Virginia.

996
01:10:56.467 --> 01:10:59.220
It spanned 912 feet above the Ohio River.

997
01:10:59.261 --> 01:11:01.847
12.100 people use this thing a day.

998
01:11:02.640 --> 01:11:05.976
And it cut out 35 miles
of extra driving each way

999
01:11:06.060 --> 01:11:08.479
between Wheeling and New Martinsville.

1000
01:11:08.562 --> 01:11:13.484
That's a combined 847.000 miles
of driving a day.

1001
01:11:14.985 --> 01:11:18.781
Or 25.410.000 miles a month.

1002
01:11:20.407 --> 01:11:26.622
And 304.920.000 miles a year saved.

1003
01:11:27.915 --> 01:11:32.086
Now. I completed that project in 1986.
That's 22 years ago.

1004
01:11:33.170 --> 01:11:35.339
So over the life of that one bridge.

1005
01:11:35.422 --> 01:11:41.512
that's 6.708.240.000 miles

1006
01:11:41.595 --> 01:11:44.390
that haven't had to be driven at...

1007
01:11:44.431 --> 01:11:46.851
What? Let's say 50 miles an hour.

1008
01:11:46.934 --> 01:11:49.019
So that's what?

1009
