Listen. I just got the tap on my shoulder.

1261
01:30:57.083 --> 01:30:59.061
and we've got some risk over here
that we need to move.

1262
01:30:59.085 --> 01:31:01.421
So today it looks like my loss is your gain.

1263
01:31:01.462 --> 01:31:02.797
<i>What kind of size are we talking?</i>

1264
01:31:02.880 --> 01:31:05.049
It should be on your screen. I just sent it.

1265
01:31:05.091 --> 01:31:06.801
<i>Jesus! Where does this land?</i>

1266
01:31:06.884 --> 01:31:08.720
- 96 on the dollar.
<i>- 91.</i>

1267
01:31:08.761 --> 01:31:10.304
All three and we're done at 94.

1268
01:31:10.388 --> 01:31:12.432
<i>Ninety-three and a half.</i>
Done.

1269
01:31:14.434 --> 01:31:15.911
{\an8}- WOMAN ON PHONE: <i>Trading.</i>
- Hello. gorgeous.

1270
01:31:15.935 --> 01:31:17.603
<i>Will. what's happening over there?</i>

1271
01:31:17.687 --> 01:31:19.188
Well. today's moving day.

1272
01:31:19.272 --> 01:31:21.065
<i>Fuck are you guys so worked up about?</i>

1273
01:31:21.107 --> 01:31:25.028
You think they tell me anything? All I know
is that today. my loss is your gain.

1274
01:31:25.111 --> 01:31:27.280
Now you're a friendly.
so I've come to you first.

1275
01:31:27.363 --> 01:31:31.284
I got 270 mil at 15 year
paying out a point and a half above par.

1276
01:31:31.325 --> 01:31:34.162
<i>- Where's it from?</i>
- Where's it from? Do you care?

1277
01:31:34.579 --> 01:31:35.788
<i>No. not really.</i>

1278
01:31:35.872 --> 01:31:37.632
<i>Now. where's the trade?
I'm hearing things...</i>

1279
01:31:37.665 --> 01:31:39.505
- Alexis...
<i>- You guys are scaring me a little.</i>

1280
01:31:39.542 --> 01:31:42.628
I'm only sharing this with you right now. 85.

1281
01:31:44.047 --> 01:31:45.089
<i>Done.</i>

1282
01:31:47.341 --> 01:31:49.677
{\an8}- MAN ON PHONE: <i>Deutsche.</i>
- It's Will Emerson.

1283
01:31:49.761 --> 01:31:51.637
{\an8}<i>Fuck you. you limey bastard.</i>

1284
01:31:51.721 --> 01:31:53.282
{\an8}Come on. are you still angry about that?

1285
01:31:53.306 --> 01:31:55.641
{\an8}<i>Word is out. I'm hanging up now.</i>

1286
01:31:57.101 --> 01:31:58.501
{\an8}- MAN ON PHONE: <i>Merrill.</i>
- Lawrence!

1287
01:31:58.561 --> 01:32:00.521
{\an8}<i>What the fuck are
you guys doing over there?</i>

1288
01:32:00.605 --> 01:32:02.916
- Just a little spring cleaning.
<i>- That is not what I'm hearing.</i>

1289
01:32:02.940 --> 01:32:04.567
All right. Lawrence. are you a buyer?

1290
01:32:04.650 --> 01:32:06.527
<i>I'm not sure anymore. Where at?</i>

1291
01:32:06.611 --> 01:32:08.422
Well. it sounds like
I should be asking you where at.

1292
01:32:08.446 --> 01:32:09.590
<i>What are we talking about here?</i>

1293
01:32:09.614 --> 01:32:11.949
Three hundred seventy-five mil
at 30 year mixed.

1294
01:32:11.991 --> 01:32:14.452
<i>- Fuck</i> me.
- Are you with me on this?

1295
01:32:15.119 --> 01:32:17.413
<i>- Sixty-three cents.</i>
- Oh. <i>fuck</i> you. <i>I'm</i> hanging <i>up.</i>

1296
01:32:17.497 --> 01:32:18.998
<i>Sixty-three.</i>

1297
01:32:19.791 --> 01:32:21.959
Let me call my man here.
I'll come back to you in five.

1298
01:32:22.001 --> 01:32:24.170
<i>It may be 55 in 5.</i>

1299
01:32:24.212 --> 01:32:27.090
Well. all right. then. Stay on the line.

1300
01:32:27.173 --> 01:32:29.342
Sam. pick up the phone.

1301
01:32:29.383 --> 01:32:31.844
- Sam. get on the line!
- MAN ON PHONE: <i>Yeah.</i>

1302
01:32:31.928 --> 01:32:33.572
- I got Lawrence at Merrill.
- Where are we?

1303
01:32:33.596 --> 01:32:35.348
- Sixty-three cents.
<i>- Jesus.</i>

1304
01:32:35.431 --> 01:32:37.850
<i>—On what?
- 375 mix 30.</i>

1305
01:32:37.892 --> 01:32:39.477
<i>Get him to 65 and hit it.</i>

1306
01:32:39.519 --> 01:32:41.521
Are you fucking kidding me? That's...

1307
01:32:41.604 --> 01:32:45.024
What is that?
That's a $131 million loss on a single trade.

1308
01:32:45.108 --> 01:32:47.276
<i>I understand. Hit it.</i>

1309
01:32:48.569 --> 01:32:51.364
{\an8}Hey. Lawrence. We're fill or kill at 65.

1310
01:32:51.697 --> 01:32:52.865
{\an8}<i>It's filled.</i>

1311
01:32:54.325 --> 01:32:56.369
(TRADING FLOOR BELL RINGS)

1312
01:33:06.420 --> 01:33:07.463
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

1313
01:33:16.514 --> 01:33:17.807
Well done.

1314
01:33:24.856 --> 01:33:26.399
I just want to give you a heads up.

1315
01:33:26.482 --> 01:33:29.735
They're going to start sending
a few people home now.

1316
01:33:32.238 --> 01:33:33.281
Now?

1317
01:33:33.364 --> 01:33:35.324
Yes. Sam. No loose ends.

1318
01:33:41.747 --> 01:33:43.082
Of course.

1319
01:33:44.417 --> 01:33:46.377
And for what it's worth.

1320
01:33:47.420 --> 01:33:49.088
you're still good.

1321
01:33:52.008 --> 01:33:55.261
Yeah. I guess someone upstairs
really likes you.

1322
01:34:49.732 --> 01:34:50.858
Sam.

1323
01:34:52.318 --> 01:34:53.861
Please. sit.

1324
01:34:53.945 --> 01:34:56.530
Congratulations are clearly in order.

1325
01:34:57.281 --> 01:34:59.492
They did the best they could.

1326
01:35:00.326 --> 01:35:04.247
You did a hell of a job.
And I thank you for it. Come on. sit.

1327
01:35:04.997 --> 01:35:06.290
Excuse me for eating.

1328
01:35:08.167 --> 01:35:09.919
but it's been a long day.

1329
01:35:10.002 --> 01:35:13.047
- Can I get you something?
- No. nothing. Thanks.

1330
01:35:16.300 --> 01:35:18.219
So. what can I do for you?

1331
01:35:18.302 --> 01:35:19.804
I want out.

1332
01:35:21.347 --> 01:35:23.266
I'm done. I want out.

1333
01:35:25.601 --> 01:35:28.497
- It's been a very difficult day for everyone.
- I need you to release my options.

1334
01:35:28.521 --> 01:35:31.148
if they're worth anything after today.
I want my bonus. I'm out.

1335
01:35:31.190 --> 01:35:34.068
You'll get your bonus. your options.
and keep your current base.

1336
01:35:34.151 --> 01:35:37.571
But I need you to stay with me
for the next 24 months. okay?

1337
01:35:41.534 --> 01:35:43.494
Oh. come on. Sam.

1338
01:35:43.536 --> 01:35:44.662
Put a smile on your face.

1339
01:35:44.704 --> 01:35:47.665
You did some good today.
You said that yourself.

1340
01:35:47.707 --> 01:35:51.043
Do you know. I'm starting to feel
a little better about this whole thing.

1341
01:35:53.212 --> 01:35:56.090
You're one of the luckiest guys
in the world. Sam.

1342
01:35:56.173 --> 01:35:58.053
Could have been digging
ditches all these years.

1343
01:35:59.218 --> 01:36:00.553
That's true.

1344
01:36:00.636 --> 01:36:04.515
And if I had. at least there'd be
some holes in the ground to show for it.

1345
01:36:06.225 --> 01:36:07.226
Jesus.

1346
01:36:07.268 --> 01:36:10.730
I just don't know
how we fucked this up quite so much.

1347
01:36:14.734 --> 01:36:16.736
When did you start feeling
so sorry for yourself?

1348
01:36:16.777 --> 01:36:18.654
It's unbearable. What?

1349
01:36:19.238 --> 01:36:22.616
So you think we might have put
a few people out of business today.

1350
01:36:22.700 --> 01:36:24.577
That's all for naught.

1351
01:36:25.494 --> 01:36:29.540
But you've been doing that every day
for almost 40 years. Sam.

1352
01:36:30.833 --> 01:36:34.754
And if this is all for naught.
then so is everything out there.

1353
01:36:37.506 --> 01:36:39.216
It's just money.

1354
01:36:39.842 --> 01:36:41.427
It's made up.

1355
01:36:42.428 --> 01:36:43.846
pieces of paper with pictures on it

1356
01:36:43.929 --> 01:36:47.850
so that we don't have to kill each other
just to get something to eat.

1357
01:36:48.434 --> 01:36:49.935
It's not wrong.

1358
01:36:50.436 --> 01:36:53.606
And it's certainly no different today
than it's ever been.

1359
01:36:54.982 --> 01:36:57.860
1637. 1797.

1360
01:36:57.943 --> 01:37:02.323
1819. 1837. 1857. 1884.

1361
01:37:04.241 --> 01:37:06.285
1901. 1907.

1362
01:37:06.744 --> 01:37:09.789
1929. 1937. 1974.

1363
01:37:10.581 --> 01:37:13.626
1987. Jesus.
Didn't that fucker fuck me up good.

1364
01:37:13.709 --> 01:37:16.837
1992. 1997. 2000.
and whatever we want to call this.

1365
01:37:16.921 --> 01:37:20.841
It's all just the same thing. over and over.
We can't help ourselves.

1366
01:37:21.675 --> 01:37:25.262
And you and I can't control it

1367
01:37:25.304 --> 01:37:28.182
or stop it or even slow it.

1368
01:37:28.265 --> 01:37:30.518
Or even ever so slightly alter it.

1369
01:37:31.477 --> 01:37:33.020
We just react.

1370
01:37:33.896 --> 01:37:36.190
And we make a lot of money
if we get it right.

1371
01:37:36.273 --> 01:37:39.235
And we get left by the side of the road
if we get it wrong.

1372
01:37:39.318 --> 01:37:41.213
And there have always been
and there always will be

1373
01:37:41.237 --> 01:37:42.917
the same percentage of winners and losers.

1374
01:37:42.988 --> 01:37:44.323
happy fucks and sad sacks.

1375
01:37:44.407 --> 01:37:47.201
fat cats and starving dogs in this world.

1376
01:37:49.245 --> 01:37:50.329
Yeah.

1377
01:37:51.831 --> 01:37:54.834
There may be more of us today
than there's ever been.

1378
01:37:54.875 --> 01:37:58.295
But the percentages.
they stay exactly the same.

1379
01:38:17.815 --> 01:38:21.652
I'll do it. John.
but not because of your little speech.

1380
01:38:21.694 --> 01:38:23.904
But because I need the money.

1381
01:38:25.281 --> 01:38:29.910
Hard to believe after all these years.
but I need the money.

1382
01:38:33.372 --> 01:38:34.641
This is the executive dining room.

1383
01:38:34.665 --> 01:38:37.293
- Do you want coffee or tea?
- No.

1384
01:38:41.505 --> 01:38:43.466
You gonna keep the kid?

1385
01:38:44.967 --> 01:38:47.386
Keep him? He's getting promoted.

1386
01:38:48.220 --> 01:38:50.055
It's all hands on deck now. Sam.

1387
01:38:50.139 --> 01:38:52.534
There's going to be a lot of money
to be made coming out of this mess.

1388
01:38:52.558 --> 01:38:56.270
and we're gonna need
all the brains we can get around here.

1389
01:39:35.267 --> 01:39:37.269
(GRUNTING)

1390
01:40:20.479 --> 01:40:21.814
Hello.

1391
01:40:23.274 --> 01:40:24.984
I've called the police.

1392
01:40:25.067 --> 01:40:26.235
Mary.

1393
01:40:26.902 --> 01:40:28.404
- Sam.
- Yep.

1394
01:40:31.240 --> 01:40:32.992
What are you doing?

1395
01:40:48.966 --> 01:40:50.926
Sam. what are you doing?

1396
01:40:53.053 --> 01:40:54.597
Ella died.

1397
01:41:20.205 --> 01:41:24.668
I was driving home from the vet
and I couldn't think of where else to go.

1398
01:41:26.170 --> 01:41:28.964
- She belongs here.
- I know.

1399
01:41:29.048 --> 01:41:31.342
But. Sam. you don't live here anymore.

1400
01:41:37.514 --> 01:41:39.224
Are you all right?

1401
01:41:40.392 --> 01:41:42.311
You don't look so good.

1402
01:41:44.104 --> 01:41:46.273
Yeah. it's been a rough day
all the way around.

1403
01:41:46.357 --> 01:41:48.150
I know. Sammy called.

1404
01:41:48.567 --> 01:41:49.610
Is he all right?

1405
01:41:49.693 --> 01:41:52.738
They got hammered. but they got out alive.

1406
01:41:52.821 --> 01:41:53.906
Good.

1407
01:42:01.747 --> 01:42:04.166
Well. I'm gonna go back inside

1408
01:42:06.335 --> 01:42:07.795
and go back to bed.

1409
01:42:09.004 --> 01:42:11.882
The alarm is on. so don't try and break in.

1410
01:42:21.266 --> 01:42:23.143
Take care of yourself.
